<http://www.spektrix.com/theisabel/event/47201AKJCKRLKLLRCPMQKNQTPDQTRPLCP> a schema:Event;
  schema:name "2025-26 Isabel Voices: The Journey";
  schema:description """
	A powerful journey of hope told through stories of healing, resilience, and light. Featuring a dramatic oratorio by Kim André Arnesen for voice and strings, this work explores urgent ecological and emotional themes. The program Includes, \"The Wound in the Water\" by Kim André Arnesen, \"The Lighthouse Keeper\" by Jake Runestad, and “Light of a Clear Blue Morning” by Dolly Parton, arr. Craig Hella Johnson.<span><br/></span>Complimentary refreshments will be offered.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Livestream Tickets are available at the link above.  Livestream Season Passes are also available, <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://www.zeffy.com/en-CA/ticketing/livestream-season-pass-2025--26\">here</a>.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>To complete your Isabel Voices 2025-26 Season Pass, select seats for all three Isabel Voices events and discount will automatically apply at checkout. 
""";
