  schema:name "Canadian League of Composers 75th Anniversary: Past Presidents’ Piano Recital with John Burge";
  schema:description """
	Canadian League of Composers 75th Anniversary: Past Presidents’ Piano Recital celebrates 75 years of Canadian creativity with a solo program curated and performed by composer and pianist John Burge. Featuring works by many of the CLC’s Past Presidents, the recital opens with Beverley McKiver’s Trillium and concludes with a stirring rendition of O Canada.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>This 75-minute tribute honours the legacy and leadership of the Canadian League of Composers through music and reflection.
""";
