<http://www.spektrix.com/theisabel/event/39601AJRRLKSVBMNJSKBSJSPPVNLVSKDK> a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Elinor Frey and Accademia de’ Dissonanti";
  schema:description """
	Elinor Frey is a leading American-Canadian cellist, gambist, and researcher. She has performed throughout the Americas and in Europe in recital and with numerous chamber ensembles and orchestras such as Rosa Barocca, Constantinople, Les idées heureuses, Il Gardellino, Tafelmusik, and the Pacific Baroque Orchestra.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Elinor Frey’s albums on the Belgian label Passacaille and Canadian label Analekta—many of which are world premiere recordings—include Giuseppe Clemente Dall’Abaco Cello Sonatas, winner of a Diapason d’Or, and Early Italian Cello Concertos, winner of the 2023 JUNO Award for Small Ensemble Classical Album of the Year. This program will include music by C. P. E. Bach and Vivaldi, and will also feature a performance by Mélisande McNabney on the Moira Hudgin harpsichord.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Accademia de’ Dissonanti</span><span><br/></span>Elinor Frey, cello and direction<span><br/></span>Boris Begelman, Joe Lanza, Maya Ito Johnson, violin 1<span><br/></span>Chloe Meyers, Jessy Dubé, Simon Alexandre, violin 2<span><br/></span>Daniel McCarthy, viola<span><br/></span>Eva Lymenstull, cello<span><br/></span>Shanti Nachtergaele, contrabass<span><br/></span>Mélisande McNabney, harpsichord<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><h2>Program</h2>C. P. E. Bach (1714 - 1788) - Cello Concerto in B-flat Major, Wq 171<span><br/></span>   Allegretto - Adagio (Cadenza) - Allegro assai<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Antonio Vivaldi (1678 - 1741) - Concerto for Strings in G Minor, RV 152<span><br/></span>   Allegro molto - Andante molto e sempre pianissimo tutti - Allegro molto<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>-Intermission-<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>J. S. Bach (1685 - 1750)  - Harpsichord Toccata in D Major, BWV 912<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Antonio Vivaldi - Concerto for Strings in D Minor, RV 127<span><br/></span>   Allegro - Largo - Allegro<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>C. P. E. Bach - Cello Concerto in A Minor, Wq 170<span><br/></span>   Allegro assai (Cadenza) - Andante (Cadenza) - Allegro assai<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Please Note: <span><br/></span>Programs are subject to change without notice.<span><br/></span>Only tickets purchased directly from the Isabel Box Office or the Isabel Website will be valid for performances presented by the Isabel Bader Centre for the Performing Arts.
""";
