  schema:name "ensemble132";
  schema:description """
	The season opens with the fearless artistry of ensemble132, a collective of world-class soloists reshaping the chamber music landscape. Through inventive, artist-crafted arrangements and boundary-crossing programs, ensemble132 breathes new life into masterworks, symphonic favourites, and unexpected gems with brilliance and imagination. The program features Kelly-Marie Murphy’s <span class=\"ItalicText\">Four Degrees of Freedom</span>, Schumann/Hong’s <span class=\"ItalicText\">Carnaval</span> for piano quartet, and Brahms’ Piano Quartet in C Minor, Op. 60.
