<http://www.spektrix.com/theisabel/event/39401AHHBKTRJHJPLGBDBSTVVRJPBTKLC> a schema:Event;
  schema:name "New Orford String Quartet with Jaeden Izik-Dzurko";
  schema:description """
	The New Orford String Quartet returns to the Isabel with two residencies in the 2025-2026 season. The first residency includes the Isabel’s Season Opener concert featuring Ian Cusson’s YUME (Dreams) for strings and Schumann’s Piano Quintet with Jaeden Izik-Dzurko, winner of the 2024 Leeds International Piano Competition and the 2024 Concours musical international de Montréal. A rising national and international star, Canadian pianist Jaeden Izik-Dzurko is praised by audiences, critics, and composers for his communicative power, refined technical command, and artistic maturity.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">New Orford String Quartet</span><span><br/></span>Jonathan Crow, violin<span><br/></span>Andrew Wan, violin<span><br/></span>Sharon Wei, viola<span><br/></span>Joseph Johnson, cello<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>With <span class=\"BoldText\">Jaeden Izik-Dzurko</span>, piano<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>This performance is supported through the generosity of Maureen Farr-Eagan and Robert Hotrum.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><h2>Program</h2>Ian Cusson - Dreams (Yume)<span><br/></span>Sunshine Through the Rain<span><br/></span>The Peach Orchard<span><br/></span>Village of the Watermills<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Felix Mendelssohn - String Quartet no. 2 <span><br/></span>Adagio - Allegro Vivace<span><br/></span>Adagio non lento<span><br/></span>Intermezzo. Allegretto con moto - Allegro di molto <span><br/></span>Presto - Adagio non lento<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>-Intermission-<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Robert Schumann - Piano Quintet in E flat major Op. 44<span><br/></span>Allegro Brilliante<span><br/></span>In moda d'una marcia: Un poco largamente - Agitato<span><br/></span>Scherzo<span><br/></span>Allegro ma non troppo <span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Please Note: <span><br/></span>Programs are subject to change without notice.<span><br/></span>Only tickets purchased directly from the Isabel Box Office or the Isabel Website will be valid for performances presented by the Isabel Bader Centre for the Performing Arts.
""";
