<http://www.spektrix.com/theisabel/event/41001AMGNGHKLQLCLRMPJKPQBNDVJPHRD> a schema:Event;
  schema:name "'Out of the Deep' - Jonathon Adams and Joanna Huszcza";
  schema:description """
	This performance features violinist Joanna Huszcza and baritone Jonathon Adams, who will be joined by a stellar group of musicians in a program titled <span class=\"ItalicText\">Out of the Deep</span>. The program is inspired by the text of Bruhns’s lament, De Profundis (“Out of the depths have I cried unto thee, O Lord…”). <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Born in “amiskwaciwâskahikan” (Edmonton), Jonathon Adams is an Indigenous (Cree-Métis) baritone whose career has taken off in North America and beyond. Recent and future solo engagements include performances with Tafelmusik Baroque Orchestra, the New York Philharmonic and the San Francisco Symphony, under Masaaki Suzuki, the Ricercar Consort and Collegium Vocale Gent, Studio de Musique Ancienne de Montréal, Servir Antico, Washington Bach Consort, and the Portland Baroque Orchestra.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Please Note: Only tickets purchased directly from the Isabel Box Office or the Isabel Website will be valid for performances presented by the Isabel Bader Centre for the Performing Arts.
""";
