<http://www.spektrix.com/theisabel/event/55801ACGDGDJSRRGCLCBTPCSLTJTBNGSM> a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Reginald Mobley with Baptiste Trotignon";
  schema:description """
	American countertenor Reginald Mobley is celebrated for his pure tone, agility, and expressive insight across Baroque, Classical, and contemporary repertoire. An award winning and GRAMMY-nominated artist, he brings historic and overlooked works to vivid life while championing diversity in music, with a program that features works spanning Black musical traditions. He is accompanied by pianist Baptiste Trotignon, an internationally acclaimed pianist and composer known for his seamless blend of jazz, classical, and improvisational artistry, whose dynamic performances have earned him numerous awards and critical acclaim worldwide.
""";
