<http://www.spektrix.com/theisabel/event/42602AVHSCVRKTVVDBKLHTRLBRGRJKKKD> a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Roomful of Teeth ";
  schema:description """
	Founded in 2009 by Brad Wells, Roomful of Teeth was incubated at the Massachusetts Museum of Contemporary Art. As the world rapidly changes, the group is cultivating deeper relationships with technology, continuing to expand the capabilities of the human voice, aiming to be unburdened by physical limitations. Roomful of Teeth is known for new collaborative projects that focus on the stories of place, home, and community. They were recognized at the 66th GRAMMY awards in 2024, winning Best Chamber Music/Small Ensemble Performance for Rough Magic (New Amsterdam Records, 2023).<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Please Note: Only tickets purchased directly from the Isabel Box Office or the Isabel Website will be valid for performances presented by the Isabel Bader Centre for the Performing Arts.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><h2>Watch Roomful of Teeth performing on NPR's Tiny Desk Concerts</h2>
""";
