<http://www.spektrix.com/theisabel/event/41202ACSLHGMMTSRKDTPMGGRBGDPBGKDT> a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Venice Baroque Orchestra - 'Vivaldi, Tartini, Veracini, Locatelli: A Bow’s Duel In Venice' ";
  schema:description """
	Founded in 1997 by Baroque scholar and harpsichordist Andrea Marcon, the Venice Baroque Orchestra is recognized as one of the premier ensembles in the world devoted to period instrument performance. This performance titled <span class=\"ItalicText\">Vivaldi, Tartini, Veracini, Locatelli: A Bow’s Duel in Venice</span>, features violinist Chouchane Siranossian, one of the leading virtuosos on the international Baroque scene today.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Please Note: Only tickets purchased directly from the Isabel Box Office or the Isabel Website will be valid for performances presented by the Isabel Bader Centre for the Performing Arts.
""";
